{"key":"post-15549957","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15549957</id>\n<content>No, he's not a tard.&amp;nbsp; Don't flame in cultivation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The leftover stump is 100% mycelium and will remain that way during the short life of the individual substrate, which is measured in weeks.&amp;nbsp; There is far less chances of contamination by leaving the stump in place rather than ripping it out.&amp;nbsp; Some strains release easily, while others leave huge divots if the grower 'twist and pulls'.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Commercial mushroom farms it should be noted, slice off mushrooms as suggested.&amp;nbsp; When one is only getting $3 to $5 per pound for fresh product, you can be sure they're going for maximum yield.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15550358</next>\n<prev>15549910</prev>\n<first>15544358</first>\n<last>15566509</last>\n<when>1324489271</when>\n<utime>12/21/11 07:41 PM</utime>\n</post>"}